{"type":"data","nodes":[{"type":"data","data":[{"debug":1},true],"uses":{}},{"type":"data","data":[{"zotero":1,"inscriptions":7},{"title":2,"author":3,"date":4,"citation":5,"uri":6},"Olumpis Olumpios ed IG, XIV, 434","Gentile","2002","\u003Cspan>L. Gentile, «Olumpis Olumpios ed IG, XIV, 434», \u003Ci>Epigraphica\u003C/i> 64 (2002): 224–29\u003C/span>","https://www.zotero.org/groups/isicily/items/CJ9QP78X",[8],{"file":9,"uri":9,"title":10,"status":11,"editionAuthor":13,"type":14,"objectType":18,"material":22,"condition":26,"layoutDesc":27,"handNote":34,"date":124,"places":129,"geo":138,"provenance":131,"provenanceGeo":142,"country":145,"region":146,"settlement":135,"repository":147,"idno":151,"textLang":154,"tmNumber":158,"facsimile":159,"letterHeights":166,"publications":167,"zotero":176,"keywords":185,"html":195,"bibl":196},"ISic001259","Statue base in honour of Olympis Mestos",{"_":12},"draft",null,{"_":15,"ana":16,"ref":17},"honorific","#function.honorific","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/typeins/lod/69.html",{"_":19,"ana":20,"ref":21},"base","#object.base","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/objtyp/lod/57.html",{"_":23,"ana":24,"ref":25},"breccia","#material.stone.breccia","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/material/lod/73.html","",{"layout":28},{"p":29,"rs":30,"damage":26},"The inscription is set out over four lines on the front face of the block on its upper half. The text is roughly centred, lines 1-3 filling the face, line 4 a single word approximately centered. Spacing between words is apparent and increases significantly in line 3.",{"_":31,"ana":32,"ref":33},"chiselled","#execution.chiselled","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/writing/lod/1",{"lettering":35,"dimensions":112},[36,37],"The letters are regular and with terminal points rather than serfis, and are inscribed in parts in what is almost a punch style, rather than a chiselled groove. Alpha has broken bar; epsilon has mostly equal legnth cross-bars; theta has a full-width cross bar; kappa has full length bars; mu has vertical first and last, three-quarter length mid-strokes; omicron is full-size; pi has eual length verticals; rho has fair-sized closed eye; sigma has horizontal top and bottom strokes; omega is rhomboid and closed.",{"_":38,"ref":39},"\n                                    Types list:\n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                ",[40,43,46,49,52,55,58,61,64,67,70,73,76,79,82,85,88,91,94,97,100,103,106,109],{"_":41,"target":42},"Α type2","https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Α-type2.html",{"_":44,"target":45},"Ε type2","https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ε-type2.html",{"_":47,"target":48},"Ε type2.3","https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ε-type2.3.html",{"_":50,"target":51},"Ε type2.3.1","https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ε-type2.3.1.html",{"_":53,"target":54},"Ε type2.3.2","https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ε-type2.3.2.html",{"_":56,"target":57},"Θ type2","https://kingsdigitallab.git